y rather than including a meaningless empty string.\n\nNow for the image in step 1 — it's labeled as an application structure example using NML. Since I can't see the actual image content, I'll reference it with the markdown image syntax instead of trying to create a text alternative.\n\nGenerating the JSON output... I'm defining what NML is—a library collection for native mobile app development that currently supports only iOS7, with plans to expand to Android and newer iOS versions. The library takes a straightforward approach to native development by directly leveraging OS capabilities, and I'm including a diagram showing how applications built with NML are structured.\n\nNML is designed to work flexibly across different development platforms, whether you're building purely native apps or using frameworks like PhoneGap or Titanium. Rather than providing platform-specific features like event handling for UI screens, I'm focusing on offering general-purpose utilities that boost development efficiency without locking developers into a particular framework.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17397,"cache_read_input_tokens":18643,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":17397,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e65a98e-6cee-4abb-a13d-553a889ae542","uuid":"4bd912cb-7a0e-4353-ac12-45cbe6e5ad1f"}
